# OLOS: The Open Network for Customer Loyalty

[![Specification Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/Status-Draft%20Framework-blue.svg)](https://github.com/olos-foundation)
[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-CC%20BY--SA%204.0-lightgrey.svg)](LICENSE)
[![Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/Version-1.0.0-green.svg)](OLOS_White_Paper_v1_with_Flow_Diagram.pdf)

> **An open, neutral interoperability protocol and settlement network for consumer reward value.**[span_1](start_span)[span_1](end_span)

OLOS establishes the missing protocol layer for customer loyalty[span_2](start_span)[span_2](end_span). It acts strictly as neutral infrastructure—not a competing loyalty platform, consumer app, or proprietary exchange[span_3](start_span)[span_3](end_span). By decoupling programmatic business rules from transactional settlement, OLOS allows tokenized loyalty value to flow safely across merchant boundaries while preserving 100% merchant data sovereignty and program control[span_4](start_span)[span_4](end_span).

