## 🎯 The OLOS Thesis: Where Open Protocols Differ

Existing loyalty systems are closed ecosystems; legacy coalitions achieve interoperability by forcing merchants into centralized commercial and data-sharing relationships[span_32](start_span)[span_32](end_span). 

OLOS explores a different approach: **Can an open, neutral protocol deliver global interoperability while allowing each merchant to retain absolute sovereignty over its currency, rules, identity, and customer relationships?**[span_33](start_span)[span_33](end_span)

The OLOS architecture enforces this thesis through a strict 7-layer separation of concerns[span_34](start_span)[span_34](end_span):


┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 1. Merchant Sovereignty  • Local rules, earn/burn rates, PII isolation   │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ 2. Trust Registry        • Identity verification & cryptographic keys    │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ 3. Protocol Layer        • Primitives: ISSUE, TRANSFER, REDEEM, CLEAR    │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ 4. Rules Engine          • Deterministic exchange & policy evaluation    │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ 5. Clearing & Netting    • Automated multilateral obligation calculation │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ 6. Settlement            • Sovereign fiat resolution via RTP/FedNow/ACH  │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ 7. Governance            • Open foundation, OIP process, dispute rules   │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

* **Merchant Sovereignty:** Merchants maintain complete control over their program economics, branding, and customer relationships[span_42](start_span)[span_42](end_span). Zero PII leaves local systems[span_43](start_span)[span_43](end_span).
* **Trust Registry:** Public-key infrastructure (PKI) and directory services establish trusted network participants without centralizing user data[span_44](start_span)[span_44](end_span).
* **Protocol Layer:** Standardizes immutable transaction events and message semantics across disparate systems[span_45](start_span)[span_45](end_span).
* **Rules Engine:** Evaluates exchange parameters and eligibility deterministically before value moves[span_46](start_span)[span_46](end_span).
* **Clearing & Netting:** Aggregates multi-party transactions to minimize capital liquidity requirements[span_47](start_span)[span_47](end_span).
* **Settlement:** Discharges netted obligations in fiat via regulated banking rails[span_48](start_span)[span_48](end_span).
* **Governance:** Standardized, non-profit stewardship defining network entry, specifications, and dispute resolution[span_49](start_span)[span_49](end_span).

