## ⚙️ Core Protocol Primitives

All value movement across the OLOS network is governed by five atomic, cryptographically signed primitives[span_50](start_span)[span_50](end_span):

* **`ISSUE`**: A merchant Gateway creates tokenized loyalty value and credits it to a cryptographic identity[span_51](start_span)[span_51](end_span).
* **`TRANSFER`**: Moves unencumbered tokenized value from one holder to another (peer-to-peer or consumer-to-merchant)[span_52](start_span)[span_52](end_span).
* **`REDEEM`**: A consumer presents value for fulfillment against goods/services; burns or locks claims on the ledger[span_53](start_span)[span_53](end_span).
* **`CLEAR`**: Internal system primitive used during multilateral netting cycles to calculate net fiat obligations[span_54](start_span)[span_54](end_span).
* **`SETTLE`**: Triggers and confirms fiat movement between merchant settlement accounts to discharge netting balances[span_55](start_span)[span_55](end_span).

